cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.CG 

The paper discusses the use of computer vision models for Bayesian posterior inference in generative models, specifically in the context of graphics rendering engines. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of discriminative computer vision models, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with graphics rendering engines, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.CG (Computer Graphics).
